$interpreted: Dagger: Fewer illegal miners these days. It seems Dylan really is keeping an eye on trespassers.
Crushfang: Understood.
Dagger: I... I'm sorry. Because of my recklessness, your right eye was...
Crushfang: To protect Totemtaff, an eye is nothing.
Dagger: ... The humans could just be playing the long con, trying to lower our defenses. I think we should...
Crushfang: Dagger, do not harbor blind hatred toward humans. Hatred leads to misjudgment.
Dagger: ...Understood.
Bear Warrior: Chieftain! The group you told us to pay special attention to last time is here again!
Crushfang: They're here!?
Illegal Miner Foreman: Have they found the hidden caves? Implement the plan...
Illegal Miner Foreman: Bears!?
Illegal Miner Foreman: Hehehehe...
Crushfang: That smirk, I remember it like it was yesterday!
Illegal Miner Foreman: Looks like only one of us is making it out of here alive.
Crushfang: ...*growl*...RARGH!!! Finally, I can avenge Razorclaw with my own claws.
Illegal Miner Foreman: Razorclaw? ... Ah yes, now I remember. You're that white bear from back then...
Illegal Miner Foreman: You should thank Razorclaw. You're chieftain now, ever since he gave his life protecting you.
Crushfang: Shut it!
Dagger: Chieftain Crushfang! Stop!
Crushfang: Why stop me! This human...
Crushfang: The emblem of the Kingdom of the Sun!?
Dagger: The human dropped it.
Dagger: We should keep him alive until we figure out what's really going on.
Crushfang: ......
Dagger: I don't know why you hate that human so much, but didn't you say that blind hatred leads to misjudgment?
Crushfang: You are right, take him back...
Crushfang: ...A grown bear now, eh...
Dagger: Hm? What did you say?
Crushfang: Nothing.
